  "text": "Since most of reports classified C. striatum as susceptible to a wide range of antibiotics [CITATION_1] , it has been suggested that a selective pressure exerted by previous antimicrobial treatment could contribute to its overgrowth. This would eventually lead this strain to become a secondary colonizer in immunocompromised hosts [CITATION_2] .",
